NAME api-security
PURPOSE
Dev's api-security-checklist IT approval gate. This skill IT build-time equivalent — what Raj self-audits before the route reaches Dev. Running this internally means Dev's review catches architectural issues, not basic security omissions. 
--- 
THE 8-ITEM CHECKLIST
Run before submitting any route for Dev review. All 8 must pass. 
CODE typescript 310CHARS
Zod Validation 
No any casting anywhere in the route No as SomeType on unvalidated data 
CODE typescript 352CHARS
Authentication 
API Key Exposure 
ALL_KEYS `process.env.APIFY_KEY`, `process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, etc.
CODE typescript 282CHARS
CRON_SECRET Validation 
CODE typescript 231CHARS
CORS Headers 
CODE typescript 258CHARS
Parameterized Queries 
CODE typescript 220CHARS
Error Response Shape 
HTTP Status Codes 
Scenario Status Invalid input (Zod fail) `400` Missing/invalid auth `401` Authenticated, wrong venture `403` Resource not found `404` Rate limit exceeded `429` + `Retry-After` header Server error `500` Dependency down (Supabase, external API) `503` + `Retry-After` header **Never** `200` on failure 
